{
  "texts": [
    "Let (N, h) be a nilsoliton with soliton derivation D, and let (η t) t∈R ⊂ Aut(N) be as in Corollary A.5.",
    "If φ ∈ Aut(N), x ∈ N are such that φ • L x commutes with η t for all t ∈ R, then x = e.Proof.",
    "It suffices to show that x = η t (x) for all t ∈ R. Indeed, since N is nilpotent and simply-connected, there exists X ∈ 𝔫 such that x = exp(X).",
    "Then X = (η t) * X, and differentiating at t = 0 we get DX = 0, from which X = 0 by definiteness of D. Now recall that for any ψ ∈ Aut(N) we have ψ • L x = L ψ(x) • ψ. Hence,φ • L x • η t = η t φ • L x = η t φη -1 t η t • L x = η t φη -1 t L ηt(x)• η t, from which we quickly deduce thatL xηt(x) -1 = φ -1 η t φη -1 t ∈ Aut(N).Evaluating at e yields xη t (x) -1 = e for all t ∈ R, and this concludes the proof.",
    "□It is known that every simply-connected nilpotent Lie group of dimension up to 6 admits a nilsoliton metric [Lau02,Wil03], but already in dimension 7 there are some which do not: see [LW11] for details about the existence and non-existence question."
  ]
}